OL,3,CMotorbike duo face wild fires and
OL,4,Ctough terrain as they bike to Cape Town
OL,6,FThe pair had been using 'fixers' or
OL,7,Flocal people to help them cross some
OL,8,Fof the more difficult borders through
OL,9,FAfrica, but after a few 'nerve-
OL,10,Fwracking' situations decided to try
OL,11,Fand go it alone.
OL,13,F"In Senegal we were stopped on the
OL,14,Froad by corrupt Police, they took our
OL,15,Fdrivers licences and visa forms and
OL,16,Fdemanded #500, it took a lot of
OL,17,Fargument to get all our documents
OL,18,Fback, in the end for #20 and even a
OL,19,Fhandshake," said Derek.
